How the app works (user flow)
1. User uploads resume PDF + pastes a job listing URL
2. Backend fetches JD, parses resume, identifies 3–5 skill/experience gaps
3. Chat opens — AI asks targeted questions about each gap
4. User answers each question in the chat field
5. After all gaps are addressed, AI confirms: "Ready to generate?"
6. User types "yes" → AI generates updated resume + cover letter + fit score
7. Results appear below the chat, downloadable as .docx& .pdf

Architecture at a Glance

Browser (Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS)
    │  POST /api/analyze  (resume PDF + JD URL)
    │  POST /api/chat     (user answers, session_id)
    │  GET  /api/results/{session_id}
    ▼
FastAPI backend
    │
    ▼
LangGraph pipeline  (SqliteSaver checkpointer, thread_id = session_id)
    │
    ├── fetch_jd_node       → scrapes URL → extracts JD text/title/company
    ├── analyze_node        → compares resume vs JD → identifies gaps list
    ├── chat_questioner     → interrupt() per gap → resumes with user answer
    │       ↑___loop_______|
    ├── confirm_node        → interrupt() for final confirmation
    └── generate_node       → resume_writer + cover_letter_writer + fit_scorer
            │
            ▼
    models_config.py   ← change provider/model per node here
    (Groq / OpenAI / Anthropic/Gemini)

